_aChangeLog.text: Fixed reflections being errors in certain parts of the map. (Some players have some issues with this). This in turn added more reflections in the map.
Added more decorations in some parts of the map
Added crates to "Stairs in Room #3 Before Elevator"
[Stripper Fix] Fixed Zombie Teleport Game Text being shown to all players.

_aLatestUpdates._sText: The stripper fix is included in the zip. Map will function regardless if you include the stripper or not.

_aChangeLog.text: Adjustments to Light Cannon's Particles
Buffed Aether Electric Field Generator (Radius increased from 384 units to 512 units, and slows zombies down by 20% when they are in the field)
Buffed Aether Light Cannon (Increased the slow from 20% to 25%, the pushback force is greater, so careful!)
Buffed Aether First Aid Kit (Zombie Push increased from 240 u/s to 260 u/s)
Nerfed Aether Fire Launcher (Damage reduced from 250 to 150)
Fixed Aether First Aid Kit zombie push not working.
Added text description of all the items when picked up.
Moved the First AFK teleport
Moved the AFK teleport of the room after tram ride
Most AFK teleports will make zombies' have 40000 HP until they leave the AFK teleport area. This is to avoid spawn killing incidents.
All zombies have a default HP of 8000HP.
More decoration is added to some areas of the map
Fixed some lighting issues on shortcut breakables
Vent shortcut after first elevator no longer allows humans to enter
Made the Ending Music louder
Fixed Svarog being able to hit himself with his own reflect beams, meaning more beams will spawn without you shooting him
Fixed Svarog's Fire Blast subtitle warning not showing the correct text.
Added an indicator for the bomb planting trigger.
One of the Override Buttons is now easier to access.
Added an console message that tells when the helicopter has arrived.

_sText:
"Aether Supplies Inc. has a goal, and their goals are to sell weapons of destruction to anyone with malicious intents. Infiltrate one of their airships and blow the airship up to avoid this reality from happening."

Map by Pasas1345
Svarog Model from Honkai: Star Rail (Hoyoverse)

Music List:
Context Sensitive - Portlight
Context Sensitive - Mask
Context Sensitive - Intel
Context Sensitive - Trouble
HoyoMix - Wildfire

Experiments with better lighting and cubemaps and a defense oriented map turned into this map. More decorated than the other maps I have published... maybe.

Includes
  • 1 Long Defense Map
  • Intro Cutscene (with a case of soft-locking if you do a specific set of actions)
  • 1 Boss
  • 4 Types of Items
  • Random Item Spawns
  • Scenic Ending

Hope you enjoy the map!
